  - group: Mepolizumab is approved and investigational.

- - name: Diethylcarbamazine
- type: drug
- source: DrugBank
- details:
  - description: An anthelmintic used primarily as the citrate in the treatment of filariasis, particularly infestations with Wucheria bancrofti or Loa loa.
  - half_life: The half-life is approximately 8 hours.
  - indication: Used for the treatment of certain filarial diseases, including tropical pulmonary eosinophilia, loiasis, and lymphatic filariasis caused by infection with <i>Wuchereria bancrofti</i>, <i>Brugia malayi</i>, or <i>Brugia timori</i>.
